# Creating a Settings File

Source: https://cs2.paradoxwikis.com/Creating_a_Settings_File

Cities: Skylines II offers a new "Settings" file format that allows modders to easily add options to their mod. As well as easily saving multiple "classes" in one file.

ThisCommunity-Made Guidewill help you set it up.

The information is subject to change as the modding tools are still being worked on.

## Definition

A "Settings" file is a`.coc`file, it's formatted as a mix of JSON and group/section names.

To use it, first create a class that holds your settings, and decorate it with the`FileLocation`attribute, this attribute will dictate the name of the`.coc`file.

You can use the same`FileLocation`value for other classes you'd like to be saved in the same file.

```
namespace MyCustomMod
{
 [FileLocation($"ModsSettings/{nameof(YourMod)}/{nameof(YourMod)}")]
 public class MySettings
 {
 public int IntSetting { get; set; } = 5;
 public bool BoolSetting { get; set; }
 }

[FileLocation($"ModsSettings/{nameof(YourMod)}/{nameof(YourMod)}")]
 public class MyOptions
 {
 public string StringSetting { get; set; }
 }
}

```

Make sure that your Settings file's name matches your ModsSettings folder name and your Log file name mentioned inthe naming guide.

