## Creating & loading a Settings file

To load your settings, simply use the`LoadSettings()`method in the`AssetDatabase.global`which takes a section name, an instance of your class, and an optional default value of that class.

```
namespace MyCustomMod
{
 public class MyMod : IMod
 {
 public static MySettings Settings { get; set; }
 public static MyOptions Options { get; set; }

public void OnLoad(UpdateSystem updateSystem)
 {
 Settings = new MySettings();
 Options = new MyOptions();

AssetDatabase.global. LoadSettings("Mod Settings Section", Settings, new MySettings());

AssetDatabase.global. LoadSettings("Mod Options Section", Options, new MyOptions());
 }
 }
}

```

In this example, two different section names are used for theMySettingsandMyOptionsto separate them in the file.

## Saving a Settings file

The game will automatically detect changes to the properties of the instance that was passed with the`LoadSettings()`call.

Once changes are detected, the game will save the file automatically.

```
Settings. BoolSetting = true;
Options. StringSetting = "Test";

```

