The Obsolete Identifiers feature allows one asset to replace another within the game. This setting is particularly useful when an asset's name has been changed or when assigning assets from a published pack on PDX Mods as replacements for local assets. When activated, a decal, surface, or netlane will substitute in saved games any existing asset that matches the "m_Name" identifier.

Example:

```
"Game. Prefabs. ObsoleteIdentifiers": {
 "PrefabIdentifiers": [
 {
 "m_Name": "Terrain Surfaces Pack Grass TTP - Clovers Surface",
 "m_Type": "SurfacePrefab"
 }
 ]
}

