## Update Phases

Every system exists within a`SystemUpdatePhase`, when creating a system in your mod's`OnCreateWorld()`, you have to specify which phase your system will update at.

You can also let your system run Before, or After an update phase if needed.

```
public class Mod : IMod
{
 public void OnLoad(UpdateSystem updateSystem)
 {
 updateSystem. UpdateBefore<MySystem1>(SystemUpdatePhase. Modification3); // Before

updateSystem. UpdateAt<MySystem2>(SystemUpdatePhase. Modification3); // At

updateSystem. UpdateAfter<MySystem3>(SystemUpdatePhase. Modification3); // After
 }
}

```

### Choosing an update phase

oadSimulation`phase is used specifically while a save-game is loading, it executes 8 times in a row.
- `SystemUpdatePhase. Serialize`phase is used specifically while a save-game or map is being saved.

- `ToolSystemBase`systems should always be on the`SystemUpdatePhase. ToolUpdate`phase.
- `TooltipSystemBase`systems should always be on the`SystemUpdatePhase. UITooltip`phase.
- `UISystemBase`systems should always be on the`SystemUpdatePhase. UIUpdate`phase.

